28/06/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Over 2,300 employees in the court system launched a three-day strike on Wednesday (June 27th). 
They are demanding higher salaries, regular bonuses and better working conditions. 
The protestors say the current monthly wage of approximately 114 euros does not cover basic costs of living. 
(Telma TV, A1 TV - 27/06/07)
